(44, 16, 29, 19, 119, 120, 120, 'trembling', 'Connection of Fear and Trembling', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of trembling in response to fear. In Acts, the trembling is a physical reaction to a divine encounter, while in Psalms, it expresses fear of God''s judgments.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 29, 23, 60, 14, 14, 'fell down before Paul and Silas', 'Bowing in Reverence', 'This connection highlights the act of bowing as a sign of reverence and submission. In Acts 16:29, the trembling jailer falls down before Paul and Silas, while Isaiah 60:14 speaks of those who despised Zion bowing down at her feet.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 29, 23, 66, 2, 2, NULL, 'Trembling Before God', 'This connection highlights the theme of trembling in both passages. The jailer in Acts 16:29 trembles before Paul and Silas, while Isaiah 66:2 speaks of those who tremble at God''s word, indicating a reverent response to divine authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 29, 24, 5, 22, 22, 'trembling', 'Connection of Trembling Before God', 'This connection highlights the theme of trembling in the presence of divine authority. In Acts, the jailer trembles before Paul and Silas, while in Jeremiah, God questions why people do not tremble at His presence.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
