(44, 16, 30, 44, 2, 37, 37, NULL, 'Inquiry About Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize a question about salvation. In Acts 16:30, the jailer asks, ''what must I do to be saved?'' while in Acts 2:37, the people inquire, ''what shall we do?'' This connection highlights the urgency and desire for guidance in matters of faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
